    public interface Registrable
    A mixin interface for an object that can be registered and unregistered. Registrable objects are usually managed by a registration manager which controls the registration process and calls the hook methods provided by this interface at appropriate time.

    All hook methods may throw a RuntimeException and it is up to the registration manager to handle the exception or propagate it further.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell
